An 18-year-old man has been arrested for allegedly raping a 68-year-old woman, Eastern Cape police said on Saturday. It is alleged that the victim was at her home at Ngobozi location, Toleni village, Butterworth, on Friday 31 March 2017. The suspect is alleged to have gained entrance through the window and accosted the victim in a clandestine manner, Captain Jackson Manatha said. The teenager was alleged to have raped the woman at about 9pm. Members of the community assisted in apprehending the suspect and handed him over to Butterworth police, Manatha said. Butterworth policing cluster commander Brigadier Trevor Mey thanked the community members in their assistance in fighting crime. The suspect would appear in the Butterworth Magistrate s Court on Monday on a rape charge. African News Agency (ANA)